<TITLE> Govt to issue bonds to fund Padma Bridge </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 13(bdnews24.com)The government is set to issue bonds to fund the Padma Bridge project from the capital market, the communication minister said in parliament on Tuesday. The minister Syed Abul Hossain said, as per the final scheme design submitted by the project consultants, the construction cost of the bridge would be nearly $2.4 billion as against the preliminary estimate of $1.5 billion. Hossain said the World Bank with other donor agencies had pledged around $460 million in project assistance. "Steps are being launched to get some of the remaining funds from the capital market by issuing bonds," the minister said. It is expected to take three years to complete the construction, he added. Hossain was replying to a question from Jatiya Party MP, ABM Ruhul Amin Hawladar. In answer to a question from another JP MP, Salma Islam, Hossain said the government has a plan to launch an electric train service on the Dhaka-Chittagong route. Steps are underway to initiate a feasibility project, he said The question-answer session of the House kicked off at 4.10pm chaired by deputy speaker Shawakat Ali. bdnews24
